document_data.Applications:
''Ironfell'' was used to make weapons, equipment, and magic items for the Warlock Knights. All Warlock Knights wore a simple ''[[ironfell ring]]'' to signify their status, and most Knights above a certain rank owned distinctive ceremonial armor also made of the substance.{{Cite dungeon/177/Realmslore: Vaasa|78}}

By the late 15{{th}} century [[DR]], the Warlock Knights were integrating ''ironfell'' into their realm's [[currency]] by creating alloys of it with traditional precious metals: the [[copper]] and ''ironfell'' alloyed coins were called [[nub (coin)|nubs]], [[silver]] and ''ironfell'' alloyed coins were called [[dirk (coin)|dirks]], [[gold]] and ''ironfell'' alloyed coins were called [[anvil (coin)|anvils]], and the [[platinum]] and ''ironfell'' alloy was minted into thin [[trade bar]]s worth 50 anvils each.

''Ironfell'' was also used to make [[golem]]-like constructs called [[shardsoul]]s.
